reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent picture quality
reviews.reviewText: I purchased this Samsung QLED TV to replace an older model Samsung TV. The main reason was because I wanted a TV with the ability to stream programs. I'm very happy with the excellent picture quality and the streaming capabilities. The only thing I dislike about the TV so far is the sound. I have to turn the volume up fairly high in order to get the sound where I like it. I would recommend adding a sound bar, which I plan to do in the future, for the better sound quality.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 6, 2023
reviews.reviewText: My mother is 76. She ordered a tv from Walt’s via Amazon. Within 3 weeks one of the LED lights went out. She called Samsung and they wanted to charge her $50 to work with a technician. She decided to just return it. I thought Walts would pay the shipping since the TV was defective. They do not. Between the packaging and the shipping it cost my mother $200 to return a defective TV. Horrible!! Do not order a TV from Walt’s!!!!!!!

reviews.reviewText: My 6 year old Vizio TV is still functioning well but it's increasingly showed the light reflection in my well lit kitchen. I decided to replace it with the more expensive Samsung TV and am so glad that we did. The color was so much brilliant and richer, the outside light didn't alter the visibility at all. The apps function well and I found it better use Samsung's remote than the Amazon's stick which seems degraded the color.
